description.narrative: The original Project development objectives are: (a) improving energy efficiency in heating buildings in order to make heating more affordable and improving functional and health environment of the users; and (b) reducing the local and global environmental impact of the use of dirty fuels for heating buildings) and monitoring indicators have remained unchanged. The principal aim of the Additional Financing is to enable the Borrower to complete the original scope of the Project (energy efficiency improvements in 3 social care buildings, 9 schools and 6 hospitals left out due to a cost overrun) and to scale up energy efficiency improvements to include: (a) rehabilitation of the heat supply system of the Nis Clinical Center along with energy efficiency improvements in all 17 contiguous buildings on the campus; complete retrofitted lighting in a number of schools and (b) energy efficiency improvements in a number of social care institutions, schools and hospitals across Serbia.

condition.narrative: The Borrower shall ensure that the Republic of Serbia implements the project in accordance with the implementation program setforth in schedule 3 of the DCA and terms and conditions set forth in EMP
The Borrower shall ensure that the Republic of Serbia maintains during the term of the project the PSC, PIU, MOH PCU, MOES PCU andCCS PCU
The Borrower shall ensure that the Republic of Serbia shall furnish to the Association certified copies of audited financialstatements and an opinion on such statements by said auditors
The Borrower shall ensure that the Republic of Serbia shall have the financial statements for each fiscal year (or other periodagreed to by the Association) audited by independent auditors
The Borrower shall prepare, under terms of reference satisfactory to the Association, and furnish to the Association, by September30, 2007, a report integrating the results of the monitoring and eval
The first Financial Monitoring Report shall be furnished to the Association not later than 45 days after the end of the firstcalendar quarter after the Effective Date

title.narrative: Quantified energy savings of the retrofitted public buildings (Schools)

baseline.value: Average annual energy consumption in 69 schools in the project scope is 373 kWh/Sq.meter based on energy audits

actual.value: Energy savings on additional 29 school buildings average 50 percent.

comment.narrative: Energy savings this winter are being monitored, an updated set of actual savings will be completed by the end of January, 2013.

title.narrative: Number of Buildings (schools, hospitals) retrofitted with energy efficiency equipment

target.value: 69 schools and 53 hospitals covered from original scope. Plus, 30 schools, 24 hospitals and 10 social buildings covered fromadditional financing scope.

comment.narrative: Final achieved target figures to be updated following on next SPN mission.

actual.value: Over the last year 29 schools, 24 hospitals and 5 social buildings have been retrofitted successfully.

comment.narrative: Construction on 20 buildings started in May, 2011.

title.narrative: Improved heat generation efficiency and reduction in heat losses in the rehabilitated network of the CCS

baseline.value: 6 coal-fired and 13 oil-fired boilers in operation with an old heat network throughout the CCS

target.value: New gas-fired CHP replaces all coal- and oil-fired boilers; primary heat network for the CCS modernized with 55 substations andcontrol system

actual.value: New gas-fired heating system infull operation: 2x16MW 1x8MW hotwater boilers; 2x5MW steamboilers; pipelines 58substations.Combined heat/powerplant (CHP)License issued. Measuredefficiency of the new system 99.4% (compared to less than40%before the Project

comment.narrative: To be updated in December , 2012 based on values at Nis CC.

title.narrative: Quantified energy savings of retrofitted public buildings (hospitals)

baseline.value: Average energy consumption in 53 hospitals in the project scope is about 395 kWh/ Sq.meter based on energy audits

actual.value: Energy Savings on 25 hospitals and 5 social care centers average 50%.

comment.narrative: CO2 emission reductions 49% on average for above hospitals, social care centers and schools.

title.narrative: Improvement in air quality through reduction of emissions at the Clinical Center of Serbia (CCS) from the new energy system

baseline.value: SOx 780 tpa; NOx 100 tpa; Ash 130 tpa; based on feasibility study

target.value: SOx 20 tpa; NOx 40 tpa; Ash 0 tpa.

actual.value: SO2, ash and soot emission is eliminated. NOx and CO2 is significantly reduced.

title.narrative: Financial savings registered by the Ministry of Health and the Clinical center of Serbia by using the new heat supply system

actual.value: CCS has saved RSD 75 million (US$ 1.05 million) for fuels by switching to gas and earned RSD 56 million (US$ 750,000) from sellingheat to others
